<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I charmed soloed in Dulak quite a bit.  I noticed all mobs in this zone have fairly high magic resistance.  Charm durations are pretty poor because of this. It also makes root, slow, and mez resist alot if not tashed, and roots will break early.  I found it to be a lot of work for so-so experience.  
<br />

<br />
If you just want experience, I'd recommend charm soloing in the grey (a shimmering rockfiend, or an undying iksar make great pets), I've had alot of fun in the grey, tons of room to kite around on charm breaks unlike in Dulak.  Also, some of the mobs in the grey drop nice vendor fodder for ~20p.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
