<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">If you're doing the boats, it's not a bad idea to clear the docks before you head up there.  This will give you a lot of room to run on charm breaks - more than enough to handle simultaneous root and charm breaks.  The mobs there are a bit lower than the ones on the boat, so a hasted, dual-wielding boat mob should have no trouble dusting all of them.  I spent 47-52 charm soloing here.  The loot is nice, the exp is nice, and it's usually pretty easy to get a good boat.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
