<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">ROFL - because kiting is normally what you do with your pet when charm breaks - running like a lunatic to get space to dump a root on it.
<br />

<br />
Mind you, running away from a broken pet is probably the last thing you want to do in Dulak. My preference is to stand my ground and channel Root through the blows. So long as your Rune is fresh you should be able to channel through root before your hasted pet chews up the last of rune.
<br />

<br />
The problem I have most with Dulak is that the zone line normally has 2 or 3 bards power kiting swarms of mobs. This has just gotten even worse since the new portal. However if you slip up the ladder in the armoury and enter the back end of Torg Mines you can normally find that zone empty.
<br />

<br />
Once in the mine entrance charm a troll and beat up the miners, just don't attack the woodelf quest NPC and watch out for the resistant miner. Last time I was there with a full group we accidently attacked the resistant miner. I'm still not sure if what happened was because of lag or he had insane HP but after 10 mins constant thrashing on him by the whole group we had done no more than 1% damage. Eventually I had to mezz him and ask the group to zone else we'd have still been beating on him till this day.
<br />

<br />
Another good point about armoury entrance to Torg Mines is that if you have to run to zone you will rarely ever zone into a train coming the other way. However in Dulak a run to zone will often dump you in amongst the entire contents of the Gunthak tunnel and the town which some bright spark just dropped off there. The only upside to that is that he's just zoned into your train as well - share the misery.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
